 Notification of the right to appeal and when the appeal must be
filed to ensure continued benefits while awaiting a hearing and
decision;

 An opportunity to examine, prior to and during the hearing, any
documents and records presented to support the decision under
appeal;

 That the hearing shall be held with reasonable promptness and
convenience, and that adequate notice shall be given as to the time
and place of the hearing;

 That the hearing shall be conducted and the decision made by a
hearing official who did not participate in making the decision
under appeal or in any previously held conference;

 That the decision of the hearing official shall be based on the
oral and documentary evidence presented at the hearing and made a
part of the hearing record;

